Future Work

As part of my ongoing learning in digital design and FPGA development, this adder will later be implemented on an FPGA development board.

The design will be connected to:

- Switches (SW) for input operands
- LEDs for displaying the sum and carry output

This will allow the functionality of the adder to be tested directly on hardware.

------------------------------------------------------------

Learning Goals

This project demonstrates several fundamental digital design concepts:

- Behavioral vs structural RTL design
- Ripple carry adder architecture
- Verilog testbench creation
- Simulation-based verification
- Signed overflow detection
- Transition from simulation to FPGA hardware implementation
